&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OXLEAS NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROTATIONAL BAND 6 OCCUPATIONAL THERAPIST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week @ 1.0 WTE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust are seeking Band 6 Occupational Therapists to join the new band 6 rotational programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity within a nine month rotation to develop a broad knowledge base in a range of clinical specialties. In this round of recruitment, we are recruiting to a rotation post available within our Older People’s Mental Health Intensive Home Treatment Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Rotational Band 6 Occupational Therapists will be offered:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Line management, professional and clinical OT supervision in line with Guidance from the Royal College of Occupational Therapists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual Personal Development Review (PDR)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional career development opportunities through training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encouragement to contribute to service development and innovation projects in the Directorates and Boroughs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to develop skills as a leader and supervisor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to attend the annual Oxleas Therapies Conference&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wider communication with the Trust via the quarterly Oxleas Occupational Therapy Newsletter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some services have evening and weekend working - the Rotational Band 6 Occupational Therapists will actively contribute to this alongside the wider Occupational Therapy service. Actual working hours are dependent on service need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAmanda Tomaszewska Job title Highly Specialist Occupational Therapist         Email address Amanda.Tomaszewska@nhs.net Telephone number02083019471&lt;/p&gt;
